definition.val: A spatiotemporal region encompassing some part of the life cycle of an organism.
Temporal interval that defines bonobo life from the prenatal stage until late adult stage.
Bonobo life cycle that starts with fertilization and ends at birth.
Bonobo developmental stage that covers the period from birth until about 8.5 years old, when individuals usually reach sexual maturity.

comments: Bonobo females reach sexual maturity by 3194 days of age (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Pan_paniscus).

definition.val: Bonobo developmental stage that covers the period from birth until about 21 months old, at which point individuals wean.
Bonobo developmental stage that covers the period from about 21 months old, when individuals wean, until about 8.5 years old, when individuals reach sexual maturity.

comments: bonobo females reach sexual maturity by 3194 days of age (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Pan_paniscus).

definition.val: Juvenile stage that refers to a bonobo who is over 21 and under 22 months old.
Juvenile stage that refers to a bonobo who is over 22 and under 23 months old.
Juvenile stage that refers to a bonobo who is over 23 and under 24 months old.
Juvenile stage that refers to a bonobo who is over 24 months and under 3 years old.

Juvenile stage that refers to a immature bonobo who is over 8 and under 9 years old.

comments: Bonobo reach sexual maturity at about 8.5 years, so we consider a 8-year-old immature stage and a a 8-year-old mature stage.

definition.val: Bonobo developmental stage that refers to a sexually mature adult bonobo, which is usually over about 8.5 years old.
Mature stage that refers to a bonobo who is over 8 and under 30 years old, the limit before geriatric age in the literature.

comments: This stage actually starts at about 8.5 years, the age of sexual maturity. See 8-year-old immature stage and 8-year-old mature stage. Geriatric bonobos are usually defined as animals with 30 years of age and older (see http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23523480 and http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2011/08/14/jungle-geriatrics.html).

Count of number of days intervening between the end of the stage and the time of fertilization according to a reference model. Note that the first day of development has the value of 1 for this property.

comments: This is a shortcut annotation that can be expanded to an OWL axiom, or to a set of OWL axioms. The exact translation has yet to be determined, and may be application-dependent.
